Here are some basic commands of linux that are important
-> ls       //for listing directory contents
-> ls -l    //for long listing to see the file or folder permissions
-> ls -a    //for listing hidden files that are in the directory
-> pwd      //for checking the current working directory
-> cd       //for changing directory
-> cd ..     //for going one directory back
-> cd ../..  //for going two directories back
-> cd -      //for going back to the directory your have exited
-> cd        //for going into home directory from any folder 
-> sudo -i   //for sifting into superuser(root)
-> passwd    //for changing passwd of root or it can be used for changing users password
-> su root   //after changing root password your can switch to root by this command
-> history   //to check history 
-> exit      // to exiting
-> uptime     //for checking current users current time of system for how long system is been running
-> whoami    //for checking user name
-> hostname   //for checking hosts name
-> man name   // man is used for checking manual of any tool
-> sudo        // if you don't want to switch to root for a specific root prevelige function simply type sudo befroe it and run it
